From: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.org>
Date: Fri, 4 Dec 2015 17:41:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 004/198] irq-bcm2836: Prevent spurious interrupts, and trap
 them early

commit 8deb5f0d9bc9e27aa42846924cbe1839f066c572 from
https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux.git

The old arch-specific IRQ macros included a dsb to ensure the
write to clear the mailbox interrupt completed before returning
from the interrupt. The BCM2836 irqchip driver needs the same
precaution to avoid spurious interrupts.

Spurious interrupts are still possible for other reasons,
though, so trap them early.
Signed-off-by: Xulin Sun <xulin.sun@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/irqchip/irq-bcm2836.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/irqchip/irq-bcm2836.c b/drivers/irqchip/irq-bcm2836.c
index dfe4a460340b..5f881829615c 100644
--- a/drivers/irqchip/irq-bcm2836.c
+++ b/drivers/irqchip/irq-bcm2836.c
@@ -144,6 +144,7 @@ __exception_irq_entry bcm2836_arm_irqchip_handle_irq(struct pt_regs *regs)
 		u32 ipi = ffs(mbox_val) - 1;
 
 		writel(1 << ipi, mailbox0);
+		dsb(sy);
 		handle_IPI(ipi, regs);
 #endif
 	} else if (stat) {
